                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <head>289. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d289fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 656.56D13/11–1557. Secret. Drafted in <gloss target="#t_UNP1"
                            >UNP</gloss>, approved in <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>, and
                        cleared in <gloss target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-11-15T16:06:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1957—4:06 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Gadel 81. Re West New Guinea. Following is decision taken by Secretary November
                    8:</p>
                <p>“Confirmed that the U.S. policy of ‘neutrality’ should be continued on the issue
                    of West New Guinea, as to sponsorship, lobbying and voting on resolutions.”</p>
                <p>Secretary’s approval of neutrality as to lobbying was supplemented by following
                    comment: “If, but only if, it can be done without becoming public, I would
                    suggest that we would not be heartbroken <pb facs="0531" n="503" xml:id="pg_503"
                    /> if there were no two-thirds majority seeming to favor Indonesia’s
                    claims.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
